        {
          "username": "Hailey Neevel",
          "rating": 1,
          "contributor_id": "115470922076692806102",
          "user_review_count": 2,
          "user_photo_count": 0,
          "user_thumbnail": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUSp_ipoKgHLDQ6RzzWz0faiZhdTh-K2MrVN0485sQ9gYs1xHBmsg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100",
          "description": "I saw Dr Cathy Schwartz today for a persistent cough and fever. She tested me for Covid and the flu, both of which came back negative. She proceeded to prescribe me an antibiotic that I found out through my pharmacy I can\u2019t take with my Lexapro. She also told me to take DayQuil, which I also can\u2019t take while on Lexapro. I wish I could say this was a one off issue, but I\u2019ve seen other reviews of people complaining about this exact same issue. Overall I felt like I wasn\u2019t listened to by her and she didn\u2019t take my medical concerns or medications into account. I will not be returning to this urgent care as I am extremely disappointed and frustrated.",
          "link": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m8!14m7!1m6!2m5!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT25SaVR6UmFVWEJPV1VaVk1VWnVlRVJVY2w4eU9HYxAB!2m1!1s0x0:0x6c517ccf47fc5af2!3m1!1s2@1:CAIQACodChtycF9oOnRiTzRaUXBOWUZVMUZueERUcl8yOGc%7C%7C?hl=en",
